Package: batchr
Title: Submit R Notebooks as Slurm Batch Jobs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Eric", "Knowles", , "edk202@nyu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Converts R, R Markdown, Quarto, and Jupyter notebooks into
    standalone R scripts and submits them to a Slurm HPC cluster as batch
    jobs. Supports selective code extraction via batch marker comments and
    generates Slurm job scripts with configurable resource directives.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 8.0.0
URL: https://github.com/eric-d-knowles/batchr
BugReports: https://github.com/eric-d-knowles/batchr/issues
Imports: 
    jsonlite,
    knitr
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
